text: Jill Clayburgh (April 30, 1944 - November 5, 2010) was an American actress. She was nominated for several Academy Awards. Clayburgh was born in New York City and died from leukemia. ==References== ==Other websites== * Category:1944 births Category:2010 deaths Category:Actors from New York City Category:American movie actors Category:American stage actors Category:American voice actors Category:American television actors Category:Deaths from leukemia
